President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring Memorial Day, May 25, 2015, as a day of prayer for permanent peace. He asks all Americans to observe a National Moment of Remembrance at 3:00 p.m. local time on Memorial Day. The President also requests that flags be flown at half-staff until noon on Memorial Day and encourages individuals to display the flag at half-staff from their homes during the morning. The proclamation honors the fallen heroes who died in service to the United States and emphasizes the need to support the troops, care for veterans, and build a nation worthy of their sacrifice.